          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. Definitions -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">2. Definitions</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><strong class="text-white">"Software"</strong> means the gpulse compiled binary, including all associated files, documentation, and updates distributed by the Author.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">"Website"</strong> means the gpulse.ai website and any subdomains thereof.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">"Service"</strong> means the Software and Website collectively.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">"Free Tier"</strong> means the local GPU monitoring features available at no charge.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">"Pro Tier"</strong> and <strong class="text-white">"Enterprise Tier"</strong> mean paid subscription plans, when available.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. License Grant -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">3. License Grant</h2>
          <p>
            Subject to your compliance with these Terms, the Author grants you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to use the compiled binary of the Software for personal or commercial GPU monitoring purposes. This license permits you to install and run the Software on devices you own or control.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            This license does not grant you any rights to the source code of the Software. The Software is distributed in compiled binary form only, and no right to access, view, or obtain the source code is implied or granted.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. Restrictions -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">4. Restrictions</h2>
          <p>You may not, and you agree not to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise attempt to derive the source code of the Software;</li>
            <li>Modify, adapt, translate, or create derivative works based on the Software;</li>
            <li>Redistribute, sublicense, lease, rent, sell, or otherwise transfer the Software to any third party;</li>
            <li>Remove, alter, or obscure any proprietary notices, labels, or marks on the Software;</li>
            <li>Use the Software to develop a competing product or service;</li>
            <li>Use the Software in any manner that violates applicable laws or regulations.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- 5. Intellectual Property -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">5. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            The Software, including all code, design, documentation, and related materials, is and shall remain the sole and exclusive property of Karthik Kirubakaran. All rights not expressly granted in these Terms are reserved.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The "gpulse" name, logo, and associated branding are trademarks of Karthik Kirubakaran. You may not use these trademarks without prior written consent, except to identify the Software in a manner consistent with reasonable nominative fair use.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            If you provide feedback, suggestions, or ideas regarding the Software, you grant the Author a perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, royalty-free license to use, modify, and incorporate such feedback without obligation or compensation to you.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 6. Free Tier -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">6. Free Tier</h2>
          <p>
            The Free Tier of the Software may be used without time limit for local GPU monitoring on devices you own or control. The Free Tier includes core monitoring features such as real-time GPU metrics, memory tracking, process monitoring, and the terminal user interface.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The Author reserves the right to modify the features included in the Free Tier at any time, provided that any material reduction in Free Tier features will be communicated with at least 30 days' notice via the Website.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 7. Pro & Enterprise Tiers -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">7. Pro and Enterprise Tiers</h2>
          <p>
            When available, Pro and Enterprise subscription tiers will be subject to a separate subscription agreement and the pricing displayed on the Website. Key terms for paid tiers:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>Subscriptions will be billed on a recurring basis through a third-party payment processor.</li>
            <li>You may cancel your subscription at any time. Access to paid features will continue through the end of the current billing period.</li>
            <li>Pricing is subject to change with at least 30 days' written notice. Continued use after a price change constitutes acceptance of the new pricing.</li>
            <li>No refunds will be issued for partial billing periods.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- 8. Data & Privacy -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">8. Data and Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            The gpulse CLI tool does not collect, transmit, or store any user data. All GPU monitoring data, including metrics, process information, and memory statistics, remains exclusively on your local machine. The Software makes no network connections for data collection, telemetry, or analytics purposes.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The only optional network functionality is the Prometheus metrics endpoint, which you must explicitly configure and which exposes data only on your local network at your discretion.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            For information about data collected by the gpulse.ai Website, please refer to our <a href="/privacy" class="text-cyan hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 9. Third-Party Software -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">9. Third-Party Software</h2>
          <p>
            The Software may incorporate open-source libraries and components, each of which is subject to its own license terms. Notices and license texts for all third-party components are included with the Software binary. Your use of these components is governed by their respective licenses. The Author makes no representations or warranties regarding third-party software beyond those provided in the applicable open-source licenses.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 10. Disclaimer of Warranties -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">10. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
