            This limitation applies regardless of the theory of liability (contract, tort, strict liability, or otherwise) and includes, without limitation, damages arising from:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>Lost or interrupted training runs, model training, or computational workloads;</li>
            <li>Data loss or corruption;</li>
            <li>Hardware damage or degradation;</li>
            <li>Inaccurate GPU metrics or failed predictions;</li>
            <li>System downtime or performance degradation.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To the extent liability cannot be fully excluded, the Author's total aggregate liability shall not exceed the amounts you have paid to the Author for the Software in the twelve (12) months preceding the event giving rise to the claim, or zero dollars ($0.00) if you are using the Free Tier.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion or limitation of certain damages. In such jurisdictions, the Author's liability shall be limited to the maximum extent permitted by law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 12. Indemnification -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">12. Indemnification</h2>
          <p>
            You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Author from and against any and all claims, damages, losses, liabilities, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or related to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
